<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-973-960  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 973 960.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  Jan 1990 v8 n1 p134(10).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software's next wave: putting the user first.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Knorr, Eric.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The next generation of microcomputer software will enable users tocreate custom applications without writing a line of code, mostlyby arranging graphic objects.andP;  Interface builders such as AppleMacintosh's HyperCard are already here, but they bear fewsimilarities with true end-user development environments that willuse integrated sets of full-featured applications as the buildingblocks of custom applications.andP;  The problem of industry standardsmust be solved before super-integrated open-architectureenvironments can emerge.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Future of ComputingSoftwareUser-FriendlinessApplications ProgrammingGraphics Languages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>